did.abstract: Salem (Essex Co.), Mass., writer and photographer, specializing in colonial American architecture. Collection contains photographs that Cousins made; the vast majority of them were taken of Salem, Mass. They are albumen prints, most in good or excellent condition. The subjects are primarily houses, churches, and public buildings of Salem, exterior and interior shots.

accessrestrict.head: Access Restrictions
accessrestrict.p: Researchers must register and agree to copyright and privacy laws before using this collection.
All or portions of this collection may be housed off-site in Duke University's Library Service Center. The library may require up to 48 hours to retrieve these materials for research use.
Please contact Research Services staff before visiting the David M. Rubenstein Rare Book & Manuscript Library to use this collection.

acqinfo.head: Provenance
acqinfo.p: The Frank Cousins Photographs were received by the David M. Rubenstein Rare Book & Manuscript Library as a gift.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Materials may not have been ordered and described beyond their original condition.

bioghist.head: Biographical Note
bioghist.p: Frank Cousins was a Salem (Essex Co.), Mass. writer and photographer, specializing in colonial American architecture.

scopecontent.head: Collection Overview
scopecontent.p: Collection contains photographs that Cousins made; the vast majority of them were taken of Salem, Mass. They are albumen prints, most in good or excellent condition. The subjects are primarily houses, churches, and public buildings of Salem, exterior and interior shots.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Collection contains photographs from albums Cousins made entitled Views of Historic Salem. Photographs are albumen prints, most in good or excellent condition. The subjects are primarily houses, churches, and public buildings of Salem, exterior and interior shots.

processinfo.head: Processing Information note
processinfo.p: Original print numbers and image captions have been retained.
